Alien fish species can inadvertently facilitate the co-invasion or establishment of parasites associated with them (
;
;
). A case in point is the channel catfish
Ictalurus punctatus (Rafinesque, 1818)
( Siluriformes : Ictaluridae ), native to North America, which was deliberately introduced into various habitats for aquaculture purposes. This introduction resulted in the co-invasion of accompanying parasites such as monogeneans, ciliates, and myxozoans (see
;
;
). Specifically, in Japan , the alien monogenean
Ligictaluridus pricei (Mueller, 1936)
( Dactylogyridae ) was reported to coestablish with
I . punctatus
in Lake Kasumigaura in the lower reaches of the Tone River system in central Honshu (
). During a parasitological examination of alien fish species within the Tone River system, not only
L . pricei
but also gill-infesting myxozoans were discovered in
I . punctatus
. Moreover, through morphological and molecular examination, these myxozoans were identified as
Henneguya postexilis Minchew, 1977
( Myxobolidae ), which had not been previously reported in Japan . Hence, this finding represents a novel record of
H . postexilis
infection in Japan .

Species of
Henneguya Th√©lohan, 1892
are fish parasitic myxospores, of which more than 250 species have been described (
). This genus is distinguished from the other member of Myxobolidae by the morphology of its symmetrical spores along with the presence of paired polar capsules and two caudal projections (
). Although the presence of two caudal projections is one of the important characters of this genus, the previous molecular phylogenetic analyses indicated that
Henneguya
is polyphyletic and the character has independently arisen several times in the Myxobolidae (
;
). In addition to the phylogenetic analysis results,
posited that the taxonomic status of the genus should be maintained until comprehensive molecular data becomes available for the type species of all genera encompassed within the Myxobolidae . In Japan , a total of 14 nominal
Henneguya species
have been reported from 10 fish species ( Table 1 ).

